WEBVTT	#Elemental Media Engine(TM) 2.17.0.0

00:00:00.00 --> 00:00:03.61
We've all heard that daily COVID cases are falling nationwide.

00:00:03.61 --> 00:00:04.98
Now, we're learning Americans are

00:00:04.98 --> 00:00:07.71
growing more optimistic about the fight against COVID.

00:00:07.71 --> 00:00:12.69
In a recent CBS News poll, 47% say things are going well,

00:00:12.69 --> 00:00:14.94
a gain of 11 points from just last month.

00:00:14.94 --> 00:00:18.03
Two major music festivals, Coachella and Stagecoach,

00:00:18.03 --> 00:00:20.08
just announced zero COVID restrictions.

00:00:20.08 --> 00:00:22.68
That means no mask mandates, proof of vaccination,

00:00:22.68 --> 00:00:24.51
or negative tests for entry.

00:00:24.51 --> 00:00:26.65
To put it all in perspective for us,

00:00:26.65 --> 00:00:29.48
we are joined by Dr. Ashish Jha, Dean of Brown University

00:00:29.48 --> 00:00:30.48
School of Public Health.

00:00:30.48 --> 00:00:31.15
Good morning.

00:00:31.15 --> 00:00:31.90
How are you doing?

00:00:31.90 --> 00:00:32.38
Good morning.

00:00:32.38 --> 00:00:32.61
I'm well.

00:00:32.61 --> 00:00:33.11
Thank you.

00:00:33.11 --> 00:00:35.22
All right, so let's get right into it.

00:00:35.22 --> 00:00:38.79
Should we be dropping the COVID-19-related restrictions,

00:00:38.79 --> 00:00:40.96
mask mandates, proof of vaccinations?

00:00:40.96 --> 00:00:41.85
What do you think?

00:00:41.85 --> 00:00:43.89
Yes, so we're first of all, in a way better place

00:00:43.89 --> 00:00:44.85
than we were even a month ago.

00:00:44.85 --> 00:00:45.35
We are.

00:00:45.35 --> 00:00:47.61
But infections are down about 80% across the country.

00:00:47.61 --> 00:00:48.87
Deaths are starting to fall.

00:00:48.87 --> 00:00:51.45
This is a good time to look at all those restrictions and say,

00:00:51.45 --> 00:00:52.66
which ones do we really need?

00:00:52.66 --> 00:00:55.70
I think mask mandates can definitely get lifted.

00:00:55.70 --> 00:00:57.39
I know vaccine mandates are going

00:00:57.39 --> 00:01:00.22
to be helpful for the long run, just keeping people vaccinated.

00:01:00.22 --> 00:01:02.80
So I think that's a good policy to have.

00:01:02.80 --> 00:01:05.34
But certainly, mask mandates, restrictions on gatherings,

00:01:05.34 --> 00:01:06.92
I think they can start getting lifted.

00:01:06.92 --> 00:01:09.06
Both the CDC director, Dr. Rochelle Walensky

00:01:09.06 --> 00:01:11.43
and President Biden both say we should not

00:01:11.43 --> 00:01:12.99
be lifting the mask mandates.

00:01:12.99 --> 00:01:14.94
Why do you think they are taking that stance?

00:01:14.94 --> 00:01:15.93
Well, I think they're be careful.

00:01:15.93 --> 00:01:18.52
And look, we always want to be careful in these moments.

00:01:18.52 --> 00:01:19.95
So I appreciate what they're both saying.

00:01:19.95 --> 00:01:21.12
Infection numbers are still high.

00:01:21.12 --> 00:01:22.62
They're coming down, but still high.

00:01:22.62 --> 00:01:23.71
Deaths are still high.

00:01:23.71 --> 00:01:25.86
So I think what they're probably reacting to is,

00:01:25.86 --> 00:01:27.25
let's wait a little bit longer.

00:01:27.25 --> 00:01:28.80
And I think I understand that.

00:01:28.80 --> 00:01:30.96
My take is, things are so much better

00:01:30.96 --> 00:01:32.73
and heading in the right direction

00:01:32.73 --> 00:01:35.40
that over the next few weeks, I think it's perfectly reasonable

00:01:35.40 --> 00:01:36.08
to pull those things.

00:01:36.08 --> 00:01:36.81
that's good news.

00:01:36.81 --> 00:01:37.56
Yeah, that is.

00:01:37.56 --> 00:01:40.77
But a recent CBS News poll found that most parents

00:01:40.77 --> 00:01:42.99
believe that kids should be required

00:01:42.99 --> 00:01:45.46
to wear their masks in school.

00:01:45.46 --> 00:01:47.83
So how should schools be looking at this?

00:01:47.83 --> 00:01:50.22
Yeah, so I'm a parent.

00:01:50.22 --> 00:01:52.29
And I-- the way I look at it is if you're

00:01:52.29 --> 00:01:55.02
in a community with high vaccination rates,

00:01:55.02 --> 00:01:57.16
infection numbers are getting low,

00:01:57.16 --> 00:01:59.79
I think it's very reasonable to lift mask mandates in schools.

00:01:59.79 --> 00:02:02.25
It's lifting of the mandates, meaning if some parents still

00:02:02.25 --> 00:02:04.56
want to send their kids masked, if kids want to wear a mask,

00:02:04.56 --> 00:02:05.73
there's no downside to that.

00:02:05.73 --> 00:02:07.54
There's no restriction on that.

00:02:07.54 --> 00:02:10.17
But I don't know that we need to be mandating it at this point.

00:02:10.17 --> 00:02:11.70
Yeah, you know, I was thinking that Sunday,

00:02:11.70 --> 00:02:13.65
watching the Super Bowl that we may look back

00:02:13.65 --> 00:02:15.98
on that Super Bowl, which felt very normal, I didn't see

00:02:15.98 --> 00:02:17.65
a lot of masks in the stands, and think,

00:02:17.65 --> 00:02:19.65
that was a milestone in the country's turn away

00:02:19.65 --> 00:02:20.34
from the virus.

00:02:20.34 --> 00:02:21.80
But what's happening here, Dr. Jha,

00:02:21.80 --> 00:02:24.26
is a lot of people are still emotionally-- they're fearful,

00:02:24.26 --> 00:02:24.76
right?

00:02:24.76 --> 00:02:26.64
They hear about removing these restrictions,

00:02:26.64 --> 00:02:28.38
and their body says, whoa, whoa, whoa.

00:02:28.38 --> 00:02:30.24
We remember how bad this was.

00:02:30.24 --> 00:02:33.42
So what do you say to people who believe in the science,

00:02:33.42 --> 00:02:35.34
like you, think you're an authority, but are

00:02:35.34 --> 00:02:37.98
like, I'm just uncomfortable, something triggers me?

00:02:37.98 --> 00:02:39.60
Yeah, no, I totally understand that.

00:02:39.60 --> 00:02:43.29
We've had two years of very, very difficult pandemic.

00:02:43.29 --> 00:02:45.96
That's why I've argued for being thoughtful and slow about this.

00:02:45.96 --> 00:02:47.67
If people want to take their time--

00:02:47.67 --> 00:02:48.75
no one's saying-- if you want to continue

00:02:48.75 --> 00:02:50.38
wearing a mask for a little bit longer,

00:02:50.38 --> 00:02:52.41
I think that's completely reasonable to do.

00:02:52.41 --> 00:02:53.85
The question is, what restrictions

00:02:53.85 --> 00:02:55.80
should the government be putting on people?

00:02:55.80 --> 00:02:58.28
In that context, I think lifting those restrictions really

00:02:58.28 --> 00:02:58.95
does make sense.

00:02:58.95 --> 00:03:01.08
And for immunocompromised, parents

00:03:01.08 --> 00:03:04.94
of immunocompromised kids, could those kids one way mask--

00:03:04.94 --> 00:03:07.48
if all the other kids were no masked, they could have one on.

00:03:07.48 --> 00:03:08.04
That'd be OK?

00:03:08.04 --> 00:03:09.46
Yeah, I think it would help a lot.

00:03:09.46 --> 00:03:11.17
So there's very good evidence that if you

00:03:11.17 --> 00:03:13.74
wear a high-quality mask, even if everybody around you

00:03:13.74 --> 00:03:16.79
is not wearing a mask, it protects you really well.

00:03:16.79 --> 00:03:18.21
So that's one way of course, we're

00:03:18.21 --> 00:03:19.38
getting treatments and other things

00:03:19.38 --> 00:03:20.61
for immunocompromised people.

00:03:20.61 --> 00:03:22.32
That'll help as well.

00:03:22.32 --> 00:03:25.74
Break down for us what it means for these children now,

00:03:25.74 --> 00:03:27.53
where they've backed off from the Pfizer

00:03:27.53 --> 00:03:29.32
or below five years old.

00:03:29.32 --> 00:03:30.82
What should parents do in that case?

00:03:30.82 --> 00:03:33.40
Yeah, first of all, I know a lot of parents of kids under five

00:03:33.40 --> 00:03:35.61
were pretty disappointed by that decision by the FDA

00:03:35.61 --> 00:03:36.48
to just hold.

00:03:36.48 --> 00:03:38.04
I think it was the right decision.

00:03:38.04 --> 00:03:40.68
Look, at the end of the day, we want to be guided by evidence.

00:03:40.68 --> 00:03:44.79
And the evidence for a vaccines 5 to 17-year-olds, terrific.

00:03:44.79 --> 00:03:46.87
The evidence just not quite in yet for under five.

00:03:46.87 --> 00:03:48.70
So what I would say is, good news infections

00:03:48.70 --> 00:03:49.38
are coming down.

00:03:49.38 --> 00:03:50.95
Continue to be careful.

00:03:50.95 --> 00:03:52.74
Let's wait for the good data, the best data

00:03:52.74 --> 00:03:54.82
that we can get before we make a decision on kids.

00:03:54.82 --> 00:03:56.49
We haven't won this fight against COVID.

00:03:56.49 --> 00:03:58.68
But it does seem like a small victory and a step

00:03:58.68 --> 00:04:00.21
in the right direction where we're at right now.

00:04:00.21 --> 00:04:01.72
To even have the conversation--

00:04:01.72 --> 00:04:02.37
Absolutely.

00:04:02.37 --> 00:04:04.65
We're in so much better place than where we were.

00:04:04.65 --> 00:04:05.76
And the good news is, we're going

00:04:05.76 --> 00:04:06.70
to continue getting better.

00:04:06.70 --> 00:04:08.70
We're going to have more therapeutics, more vaccines.

00:04:08.70 --> 00:04:09.49
I think we're in good shape.

00:04:09.49 --> 00:04:10.16
We got vaccines.

00:04:10.16 --> 00:04:10.98
We got treatments.

00:04:10.98 --> 00:04:11.86
We got immunity.

00:04:11.86 --> 00:04:12.57
And we got to go.

00:04:12.57 --> 00:04:14.07
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:14.07 --> 00:04:14.77
I mean, come on.

00:04:14.77 --> 00:04:15.60
Let's have a moment.

00:04:15.60 --> 00:04:16.35
It's a good thing.

00:04:16.35 --> 00:04:17.01
OK.

00:04:17.01 --> 00:04:17.51
All right.

00:04:17.51 --> 00:04:19.89
We're having our moment, Dr. Jha, thank you so much.

00:04:19.89 --> 00:04:21.44
Thank you.